1
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:01:07,923 --> 00:01:09,633
-Is that a person?
-I think so.

3
00:01:09,716 --> 00:01:11,593
-What the…
-Hey!

4
00:01:11,677 --> 00:01:12,969
Excuse me!

5
00:01:13,512 --> 00:01:15,639
-There's blood. Oh my God.
-Hello? We need an ambulance.

6
00:01:15,722 --> 00:01:18,058
Someone has collapsed on the ground here.

7
00:01:18,141 --> 00:01:19,935
Abdominal stab wound. Bleeding won't stop.

8
00:01:20,018 --> 00:01:21,603
Prepare a transfusion and page trauma.

9
00:01:21,687 --> 00:01:22,896
Cha Se-gye!

10
00:01:22,979 --> 00:01:24,189
Do not die, Cha Se-gye.

11
00:01:27,317 --> 00:01:28,235
<i>Don't cry.</i>

12
00:01:32,989 --> 00:01:34,366
<i>I need to get up.</i>

13
00:01:39,579 --> 00:01:41,164
<i>I can't leave her…</i>

14
00:01:41,873 --> 00:01:44,501
Stay with us, sir!

15
00:01:44,584 --> 00:01:47,087
-Blood pressure's still dropping.
<i>-Not like this…</i>

16
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:49,089
Heart rate, 120. I'll start fluids.

17
00:01:49,172 --> 00:01:50,382
Start CPR.

18
00:02:18,118 --> 00:02:20,704
You all must be weary
from the long journey.

19
00:02:22,122 --> 00:02:24,124
This is a royal letter from His Majesty.

20
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:27,461
The Queen Dowager also sent
some restorative soup.

21
00:02:27,544 --> 00:02:29,337
I anticipated a royal edict,

22
00:02:29,963 --> 00:02:31,590
not a letter and soup.

23
00:02:32,257 --> 00:02:34,468
I suppose I am not destined to die yet.

24
00:02:50,525 --> 00:02:52,027
<i>Drink it.</i>

25
00:02:52,110 --> 00:02:53,487
<i>Die as a sinner.</i>

26
00:02:54,154 --> 00:02:56,031
<i>Then the girl will live.</i>

27
00:02:59,659 --> 00:03:02,913
I must entrust you
to an unreliable promise.

28
00:03:36,988 --> 00:03:40,158
<i>Even if this is the end,</i>
<i>I cannot say it was a bad life.</i>

29
00:03:40,826 --> 00:03:43,495
<i>A royal who could never be sovereign.</i>

30
00:03:43,578 --> 00:03:45,956
<i>I was never destined</i>
<i>to live out a full life.</i>

31
00:03:46,706 --> 00:03:49,584
<i>Still, departing this life with the one</i>
<i>I treasure most kept safe…</i>

32
00:03:49,668 --> 00:03:51,920
<i>Is that not a rather</i>
<i>fitting end for a man?</i>

33
00:04:13,984 --> 00:04:15,193
What is the meaning of this?

34
00:04:15,277 --> 00:04:16,862
You are a dead man anyway.

35
00:04:16,945 --> 00:04:19,447
This manner of death is
His Majesty's will.

36
00:04:19,531 --> 00:04:21,408
The tragic prince in exile
who fell to bandits

37
00:04:21,491 --> 00:04:23,034
and vanished without a trace.

38
00:04:23,535 --> 00:04:25,453
That is how history will remember you.

39
00:04:25,537 --> 00:04:26,663
You scoundrel!

40
00:04:53,732 --> 00:04:54,733
<i>I will</i>

41
00:04:55,483 --> 00:04:56,693
<i>save you this time.</i>

42
00:04:58,153 --> 00:05:05,118
EPISODE 14
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

43
00:05:31,186 --> 00:05:33,396
Hey, Dan-sim.

44
00:05:34,147 --> 00:05:35,231
Kang Dan-sim.

45
00:05:57,837 --> 00:05:58,797
This is

46
00:05:59,798 --> 00:06:00,799
the palace.

47
00:06:00,882 --> 00:06:02,467
Hey, are you okay?

48
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,470
I am back.

49
00:06:06,179 --> 00:06:07,430
In Joseon.

50
00:06:08,098 --> 00:06:09,641
<i>You can save him.</i>

51
00:06:10,183 --> 00:06:12,978
If you, Your Highness,
sever the chain of fate.

52
00:06:13,061 --> 00:06:14,270
The chain of fate?

53
00:06:14,354 --> 00:06:16,815
Your beloved is fated to die,

54
00:06:16,898 --> 00:06:19,234
be it in Joseon or here.

55
00:06:19,317 --> 00:06:22,278
So you must go back
and save the Grand Prince.

56
00:06:23,321 --> 00:06:25,824
Then this fate will not be repeated.

57
00:06:25,907 --> 00:06:29,494
<i>You only have to pay a small price.</i>

58
00:06:36,334 --> 00:06:39,587
Hey, why are you in such a daze today?

59
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:42,799
You…

60
00:06:43,383 --> 00:06:44,426
You wench.

61
00:06:44,968 --> 00:06:46,177
What are you doing here?

62
00:06:51,474 --> 00:06:52,475
Your clothes…

63
00:06:53,476 --> 00:06:55,145
You were also a bond from a past life?

64
00:06:55,228 --> 00:06:57,564
Hold on. Were you sleeping?

65
00:06:59,774 --> 00:07:02,027
<i>I never knew her in Joseon.</i>

66
00:07:02,736 --> 00:07:03,945
<i>Did something change?</i>

67
00:07:06,031 --> 00:07:07,991
<i>I am definitely inside the palace.</i>

68
00:07:08,658 --> 00:07:09,743
Where are we?

69
00:07:11,161 --> 00:07:13,747
Where else? The Queen Dowager's quarters.

70
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,290
JAGYEONGJEON HALL

71
00:07:15,373 --> 00:07:17,834
The nerve you have.

72
00:07:18,418 --> 00:07:20,378
How could a palace attendant fall asleep?

73
00:07:20,462 --> 00:07:21,796
The Queen Dowager's quarters.

74
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,048
Palace attendant.

75
00:07:24,591 --> 00:07:25,967
<i>The past has changed.</i>

76
00:07:26,509 --> 00:07:27,469
<i>In that case…</i>

77
00:07:28,803 --> 00:07:30,638
<i>I can change other things too.</i>

78
00:07:33,266 --> 00:07:36,144
Announcing His Majesty!

79
00:07:44,152 --> 00:07:45,111
<i>It is him.</i>

80
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,998
Do not just stand there.

81
00:07:57,082 --> 00:07:58,500
Open the doors at once.

82
00:08:00,502 --> 00:08:01,753
Yes, of course.

83
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,799
You come in as well.

84
00:08:20,688 --> 00:08:22,690
<i>He became king in the meantime.</i>

85
00:08:23,858 --> 00:08:25,777
<i>The Queen Dowager is still alive.</i>

86
00:08:26,653 --> 00:08:29,030
<i>It has not even been a year</i>
<i>since his ascension.</i>

87
00:08:30,698 --> 00:08:32,784
<i>She fell ill upon hearing</i>
<i>of the Grand Prince's death</i>

88
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:34,285
<i>and passed a few days later.</i>

89
00:08:35,203 --> 00:08:36,704
<i>If the Queen Dowager is alive,</i>

90
00:08:37,372 --> 00:08:38,581
<i>he must still be…</i>

91
00:08:38,665 --> 00:08:41,376
Around this time of year, the Grand Prince

92
00:08:41,459 --> 00:08:43,294
would always fall terribly ill.

93
00:08:45,421 --> 00:08:46,881
To think of what hardships

94
00:08:47,507 --> 00:08:49,509
he must be enduring in that harsh place…

95
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,931
I can only be grateful that His Majesty

96
00:08:55,557 --> 00:08:57,142
has heeded a mother's heart.

97
00:08:57,225 --> 00:08:59,060
It weighs heavily on my heart as well.

98
00:08:59,144 --> 00:09:02,188
I intended to send him a letter
within the coming days.

99
00:09:02,272 --> 00:09:04,065
I will also have them deliver

100
00:09:04,149 --> 00:09:06,234
the restorative soup
you prepared for him.

101
00:09:09,779 --> 00:09:12,574
She shall deliver it safely.

102
00:09:15,285 --> 00:09:16,327
Your Majesty

103
00:09:18,121 --> 00:09:20,290
wishes to send me to the Grand Prince?

104
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:24,252
Yes. I heard you were once assigned
to Seonghyeon Pavilion.

105
00:09:24,335 --> 00:09:25,879
Deliver it safely.

106
00:09:25,962 --> 00:09:29,215
I am sure seeing a familiar face
should put him at ease.

107
00:09:29,299 --> 00:09:33,303
And be sure to observe
the Grand Prince's condition closely.

108
00:09:34,262 --> 00:09:35,471
<i>He is still alive.</i>

109
00:09:36,931 --> 00:09:38,057
<i>I can save him.</i>

110
00:09:41,269 --> 00:09:44,147
He was stabbed in the abdomen,
damaging his kidney.

111
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:47,817
We performed emergency surgery,
but he's in hemorrhagic shock.

112
00:09:47,901 --> 00:09:51,362
Right now, he just needs to make it
through the night.

113
00:10:04,417 --> 00:10:05,585
<i>You are here.</i>

114
00:10:26,481 --> 00:10:28,608
You all must be weary
from the long journey.

115
00:10:29,692 --> 00:10:30,652
<i>He is still alive.</i>

116
00:10:32,153 --> 00:10:34,572
This is a royal letter from His Majesty.

117
00:10:34,656 --> 00:10:37,408
The Queen Dowager also sent
some restorative soup.

118
00:10:37,492 --> 00:10:39,285
I anticipated a royal edict,

119
00:10:39,994 --> 00:10:41,579
not a letter and soup.

120
00:10:43,957 --> 00:10:46,501
I suppose I am not destined to die yet.

121
00:10:50,088 --> 00:10:52,090
I shall prepare the table shortly.

122
00:11:13,027 --> 00:11:14,904
Why have you become so quiet?

123
00:11:15,822 --> 00:11:18,533
I have longed for
that endless chatter of yours.

124
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:28,209
Your Highness

125
00:11:29,711 --> 00:11:31,796
has not changed in the slightest.

126
00:11:35,466 --> 00:11:37,093
It is as if time had stopped.

127
00:11:46,394 --> 00:11:47,812
But you…

128
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,607
seem to have changed a bit.

129
00:11:54,027 --> 00:11:56,696
Your eyes and spirit have grown stronger.

130
00:12:00,283 --> 00:12:01,534
But why did you come?

131
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,119
I was taken aback

132
00:12:03,202 --> 00:12:06,539
to hear that the Queen Mother would be
sending you, of all her attendants.

133
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:12,086
She shall deliver it safely.

134
00:12:13,129 --> 00:12:15,757
<i>Anjong must have sent me for a reason.</i>

135
00:12:18,051 --> 00:12:21,387
What does the letter say?
Is he asking how you are?

136
00:12:21,471 --> 00:12:22,930
That is none of your concern.

137
00:12:23,014 --> 00:12:25,433
Even if I am a sinner,

138
00:12:25,516 --> 00:12:29,062
I would not show a letter
from His Majesty to a mere court lady.

139
00:12:29,145 --> 00:12:30,188
<i>I am bait.</i>

140
00:12:30,271 --> 00:12:32,315
<i>He sent me here to use me as bait.</i>

141
00:12:35,234 --> 00:12:36,569
<i>Then,</i>

142
00:12:37,195 --> 00:12:38,321
<i>that must be…</i>

143
00:12:40,823 --> 00:12:43,242
You must not drink that. It is poison!

144
00:12:48,373 --> 00:12:49,457
Poison?

145
00:12:50,708 --> 00:12:52,752
Do you dare slander
Her Majesty the Queen Mother?

146
00:12:52,835 --> 00:12:54,337
Do you not see?

147
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:56,047
I was used as bait.

148
00:12:56,589 --> 00:12:58,424
To make you quietly drink
the poison and die.

149
00:12:58,508 --> 00:12:59,467
What?

150
00:12:59,967 --> 00:13:01,177
Bait?

151
00:13:02,303 --> 00:13:03,513
Who do you think you are?

152
00:13:04,347 --> 00:13:06,349
Just because we shared
some banter as "companions,"

153
00:13:06,432 --> 00:13:08,893
do you truly think
that makes you something to me?

154
00:13:11,354 --> 00:13:12,688
I was happy.

155
00:13:12,772 --> 00:13:14,399
I was just a court lady

156
00:13:14,482 --> 00:13:17,193
with no one to confide in but a stray dog.

157
00:13:17,276 --> 00:13:19,362
I was happy when you offered
to be my companion.

158
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:22,448
You were the first

159
00:13:23,908 --> 00:13:26,536
to ever peer into the heart
of this lowly court lady.

160
00:13:29,997 --> 00:13:31,290
Compose yourself.

161
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:33,626
I have never once cared for you.

162
00:13:33,709 --> 00:13:36,421
I have no need
for the affections of a mere court lady.

163
00:13:37,672 --> 00:13:38,881
So bury them.

164
00:13:40,508 --> 00:13:41,634
Me.

165
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:44,887
And your memories.

166
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:46,389
Did you know?

167
00:13:48,182 --> 00:13:50,476
I like the rain now.

168
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:52,812
I have come to appreciate
its cleansing chill.

169
00:13:55,064 --> 00:13:56,732
It reminds me that I am alive.

170
00:13:57,316 --> 00:13:59,235
<i>Now feel it for yourself.</i>

171
00:13:59,318 --> 00:14:00,445
<i>This cleansing chill.</i>

172
00:14:03,739 --> 00:14:04,991
I am alive.

173
00:14:05,074 --> 00:14:06,242
<i>I survived.</i>

174
00:14:09,203 --> 00:14:12,331
Even when I thought I wanted to die,
I actually wanted to live.

175
00:14:13,207 --> 00:14:15,126
I did not want to live as I had been.

176
00:14:15,626 --> 00:14:17,462
But I did not want to die.

177
00:14:18,045 --> 00:14:19,005
That is

178
00:14:20,089 --> 00:14:21,757
what you awakened in me.

179
00:14:22,758 --> 00:14:24,260
-My will to live.
-You--

180
00:14:24,343 --> 00:14:27,180
Should this life be unbearable,
there are other ways to live.

181
00:14:27,263 --> 00:14:28,681
You must find yourself a new world.

182
00:14:28,764 --> 00:14:31,017
Be it Qing or another foreign land.
Anywhere but here.

183
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,727
You must escape from this place.

184
00:14:44,113 --> 00:14:46,240
I thought your lips had grown
heavy with silence,

185
00:14:46,324 --> 00:14:47,825
but they could not be lighter.

186
00:14:51,329 --> 00:14:53,789
How you prattle on so thoughtlessly.

187
00:14:59,629 --> 00:15:01,339
Then again, that is you.

188
00:15:06,219 --> 00:15:07,678
Ever the same.

189
00:15:41,921 --> 00:15:43,506
Did my brother send you?

190
00:15:43,589 --> 00:15:45,841
Did he tell you
to bring his brother's head?

191
00:15:45,925 --> 00:15:46,968
Just consider us bandits

192
00:15:47,051 --> 00:15:49,220
who left empty-handed
after foolishly following

193
00:15:49,303 --> 00:15:51,639
some soldiers and palace servants
into the mountains.

194
00:15:51,722 --> 00:15:54,308
Would that not be better
for your peace of mind?

195
00:15:57,562 --> 00:15:58,521
No.

196
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:20,376
This is your chance to flee.

197
00:16:20,459 --> 00:16:21,460
No, we must go together.

198
00:16:21,544 --> 00:16:23,379
There is no time. You must hide.

199
00:16:23,462 --> 00:16:24,589
Did I not tell you?

200
00:16:24,672 --> 00:16:26,215
I am trying to save you.

201
00:16:26,299 --> 00:16:28,342
<i>He</i> will only live
if Your Highness survives.

202
00:16:32,179 --> 00:16:33,598
-"He"?
-Yes.

203
00:16:34,307 --> 00:16:35,182
He is

204
00:16:35,766 --> 00:16:37,476
more precious than life to me.

205
00:16:38,019 --> 00:16:39,353
I smiled because of him.

206
00:16:39,437 --> 00:16:41,355
I was finally able to breathe.

207
00:16:41,439 --> 00:16:44,567
Just as Your Highness once saved me,
I too wish to save him.

208
00:16:45,985 --> 00:16:47,486
I cannot give up now.

209
00:16:50,489 --> 00:16:52,491
You have found someone like that?

210
00:16:52,575 --> 00:16:54,285
Now I understand.

211
00:16:54,368 --> 00:16:57,121
Why your eyes have come
to hold such courage.

212
00:17:06,464 --> 00:17:08,049
Do not worry.

213
00:17:11,427 --> 00:17:12,803
I shall live.

214
00:17:14,889 --> 00:17:16,849
I am so widely despised…

215
00:17:18,517 --> 00:17:19,644
I will not die easily.

216
00:18:01,227 --> 00:18:02,770
<i>In the end…</i>

217
00:18:26,502 --> 00:18:27,586
No…

218
00:18:28,212 --> 00:18:29,171
Shin Seo-ri.

219
00:18:29,255 --> 00:18:31,006
Se-gye, are you awake?

220
00:18:31,549 --> 00:18:32,800
Sir?

221
00:18:32,883 --> 00:18:34,760
I'll go get the doctor.

222
00:18:36,804 --> 00:18:38,681
Se-gye, are you okay?

223
00:18:40,975 --> 00:18:43,269
What happened? Shin Seo-ri…

224
00:18:43,894 --> 00:18:46,230
You shouldn't move yet.
You'll tear your stitches.

225
00:18:46,939 --> 00:18:49,859
You were just moved from the ICU.

226
00:18:49,942 --> 00:18:51,944
The doctor said you need absolute rest.

227
00:18:52,695 --> 00:18:54,405
He just woke up.

228
00:18:54,488 --> 00:18:56,449
How are you feeling, sir?

229
00:18:57,032 --> 00:18:58,784
-Mr. Son.
-Sir.

230
00:18:59,535 --> 00:19:00,619
Where is Shin Seo-ri?

231
00:19:01,871 --> 00:19:02,788
Shin Seo-ri.

232
00:19:03,622 --> 00:19:06,041
Why are you two here?

233
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,210
Stop wasting time with me. Go see Se-gye.

234
00:19:08,294 --> 00:19:10,379
Go and talk to his doctor.

235
00:19:10,463 --> 00:19:12,798
Tae-hee said she'd call
when Se-gye wakes up.

236
00:19:12,882 --> 00:19:15,342
Is she his family? No, you are!

237
00:19:15,426 --> 00:19:17,052
He doesn't even have his parents around.

238
00:19:17,136 --> 00:19:20,765
He is your one and only nephew,
and you can't even look after him?

239
00:19:20,848 --> 00:19:22,683
We didn't have
a father growing up, either.

240
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:25,603
You only cared about Jin-u.
You never even looked our way.

241
00:19:25,686 --> 00:19:28,355
How can we show him love
when we never received any?

242
00:19:28,439 --> 00:19:30,900
Why would you go bringing this up now?

243
00:19:30,983 --> 00:19:32,526
You're upsetting Father.

244
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:34,195
Always going on about that damn grandson!

245
00:19:34,278 --> 00:19:36,822
Father. We're your children too.

246
00:19:36,906 --> 00:19:38,365
Stop living in the past.

247
00:19:38,449 --> 00:19:40,701
Try looking forward,
or even just around you for once.

248
00:19:40,785 --> 00:19:42,536
You should try it out one of these days!

249
00:19:43,162 --> 00:19:44,789
Why that little…

250
00:19:55,466 --> 00:19:57,760
When will he be able to be discharged?

251
00:19:57,843 --> 00:19:59,136
You're quite impatient.

252
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:01,013
He just woke up.
We'll have to monitor him.

253
00:20:02,389 --> 00:20:03,349
Sir?

254
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,733
<i>I can't find Ms. Shin.</i>

255
00:20:12,817 --> 00:20:14,985
<i>She's not at the restaurant</i>
<i>or at her place.</i>

256
00:20:15,069 --> 00:20:16,195
<i>She's unreachable.</i>

257
00:20:16,278 --> 00:20:18,656
The police don't really have
anything either.

258
00:20:18,739 --> 00:20:21,116
Nothing but suspicion
and circumstantial evidence.

259
00:20:21,992 --> 00:20:24,829
Secure the interrogation room recording
and prepare a response.

260
00:20:24,912 --> 00:20:27,748
Frame it as a wrongful investigation
and incompetent police.

261
00:20:27,832 --> 00:20:29,416
-There he is.
-He's here!

262
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,918
Chairman Choi, regarding the nurse…

263
00:20:31,001 --> 00:20:33,546
-Do you admit to the charges?
-Do you have anything to say?

264
00:20:33,629 --> 00:20:34,547
Care to comment?

265
00:20:34,630 --> 00:20:36,590
Mr. Cha Se-gye was attacked last night…

266
00:20:39,218 --> 00:20:41,345
Where is Shin Seo-ri? What did you do?

267
00:20:42,304 --> 00:20:44,515
Se-gye, you're awake!

268
00:20:44,598 --> 00:20:46,392
Thank goodness.

269
00:20:47,017 --> 00:20:48,352
Tell me where she is.

270
00:20:51,647 --> 00:20:53,774
Hey, why would you ask me about her?

271
00:20:55,067 --> 00:20:56,402
You should have protected her.

272
00:20:56,485 --> 00:20:57,945
What, can you not find her?

273
00:20:58,028 --> 00:20:59,071
Did she run away?

274
00:21:01,907 --> 00:21:02,783
Then again,

275
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:05,911
I suppose there is always a dagger
hanging over those who stand beside you.

276
00:21:05,995 --> 00:21:07,830
Anyone in their right mind

277
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:09,540
would run.

278
00:21:09,623 --> 00:21:10,708
You son of a…

279
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:13,210
Se-gye, are you okay?

280
00:21:16,171 --> 00:21:18,382
Seriously, I had nothing to do with her.

281
00:21:19,174 --> 00:21:20,092
You'd better find her.

282
00:21:21,218 --> 00:21:22,720
Before I do.

283
00:21:23,721 --> 00:21:25,598
-Are you okay?
-Why you little…

284
00:21:25,681 --> 00:21:26,807
Mr. Cha Se-gye!

285
00:21:27,308 --> 00:21:28,726
Are you okay, sir?

286
00:21:28,809 --> 00:21:30,227
-You piece of…
-Enough!

287
00:21:30,311 --> 00:21:31,270
Sir.

288
00:21:35,691 --> 00:21:38,152
We can file a missing person report,

289
00:21:38,235 --> 00:21:40,195
but without foul play,
we can't investigate.

290
00:21:40,279 --> 00:21:43,490
We could act right away
if an immediate family member filed…

291
00:21:43,574 --> 00:21:44,825
She doesn't have any family.

292
00:21:44,909 --> 00:21:46,785
Her grandmother passed away recently.

293
00:21:51,582 --> 00:21:53,125
Please do something.

294
00:21:59,256 --> 00:22:00,257
Mr. Cha.

295
00:22:01,884 --> 00:22:03,719
You don't look so good.

296
00:22:04,428 --> 00:22:05,554
Are you okay?

297
00:22:07,806 --> 00:22:11,477
<i>I suppose there is always a dagger</i>
<i>hanging over those who stand beside you.</i>

298
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:13,520
Anyone in their right mind

299
00:22:14,355 --> 00:22:15,439
would run.

300
00:22:20,194 --> 00:22:22,321
Mr. Cha! Are you okay?

301
00:22:22,404 --> 00:22:24,281
What are you even doing here?

302
00:22:26,951 --> 00:22:28,077
I can't find her.

303
00:22:30,287 --> 00:22:32,414
Did she really run away?

304
00:22:33,958 --> 00:22:36,001
It'd be a relief if she just ran away.

305
00:22:36,085 --> 00:22:38,128
As long as she's safe.

306
00:22:39,755 --> 00:22:40,839
Sir, let's just…

307
00:22:43,467 --> 00:22:46,053
I don't think you should be
worrying about Ms. Shin right now.

308
00:22:46,136 --> 00:22:47,513
Let's get you back to the hospital.

309
00:22:47,596 --> 00:22:49,264
Easy. Careful.

310
00:22:53,268 --> 00:22:55,437
Why haven't the police made any progress?

311
00:22:55,521 --> 00:22:57,106
I can't live with all this anxiety.

312
00:22:57,189 --> 00:23:00,067
The police are still investigating.
Let's just be patient.

313
00:23:02,736 --> 00:23:05,322
Goodness. Are you feeling okay?

314
00:23:07,741 --> 00:23:10,160
Are you sure you should be
out and about like this?

315
00:23:11,829 --> 00:23:13,455
I can't find Shin Seo-ri.

316
00:23:14,081 --> 00:23:16,750
I think something happened to her.

317
00:23:18,877 --> 00:23:20,045
But I can't find her.

318
00:23:27,469 --> 00:23:29,304
Please help me, Grandfather.

319
00:23:45,654 --> 00:23:47,156
<i>We found Ms. Shin Seo-ri.</i>

320
00:23:47,823 --> 00:23:49,116
<i>We found her,</i>

321
00:23:49,992 --> 00:23:50,951
<i>but right now she's…</i>

322
00:23:51,035 --> 00:23:52,745
-Excuse me.
-Pardon me.

323
00:24:16,769 --> 00:24:18,145
<i>They say she's unconscious.</i>

324
00:24:27,946 --> 00:24:29,615
Are you her guardian?

325
00:24:32,159 --> 00:24:33,118
What happened to her?

326
00:24:33,202 --> 00:24:34,536
We thought it was temporary,

327
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:36,622
but she's not responding.

328
00:24:36,705 --> 00:24:38,207
It took us a while to identify her.

329
00:24:38,290 --> 00:24:41,502
You should transfer her
to a larger hospital for a thorough exam.

330
00:24:42,252 --> 00:24:43,712
Shin Seo-ri, why…

331
00:25:12,658 --> 00:25:15,119
I offer you my sincerest congratulations.

332
00:25:18,831 --> 00:25:20,833
Your punishment has ended.

333
00:25:22,084 --> 00:25:23,961
Now, you may be free from your pain.

334
00:25:25,003 --> 00:25:26,088
Pain…

335
00:25:26,713 --> 00:25:28,924
Sever every knotted thread of connection,

336
00:25:29,007 --> 00:25:31,510
whether ill-fated or destined.

337
00:25:32,261 --> 00:25:35,305
Then you shall never again lose
the ones you hold dear

338
00:25:35,389 --> 00:25:37,850
or shed another tear for them.

339
00:25:37,933 --> 00:25:40,978
You have endured enough suffering.

340
00:25:43,105 --> 00:25:44,148
Yes.

341
00:25:46,275 --> 00:25:47,192
I suffered.

342
00:25:47,276 --> 00:25:49,361
It was agony beyond what I could bear.

343
00:25:49,444 --> 00:25:51,947
You need not endure it any longer.

344
00:25:52,698 --> 00:25:54,533
Until you are ready
to pass on to the afterlife,

345
00:25:54,616 --> 00:25:57,953
you may simply stay here
and find your peace.

346
00:25:58,036 --> 00:26:01,165
This is a reward
bestowed upon you by the heavens.

347
00:26:07,713 --> 00:26:08,839
It is peaceful.

348
00:26:11,884 --> 00:26:13,343
Not a breath of wind.

349
00:26:16,555 --> 00:26:17,890
It is so quiet.

350
00:26:17,973 --> 00:26:19,766
And so, the vixen
chose to remain in a place

351
00:26:19,850 --> 00:26:21,226
that was neither past nor present,

352
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:24,104
neither the world of the dead
nor the world of the living.

353
00:26:24,188 --> 00:26:25,689
Because the soul-piercing pain

354
00:26:25,772 --> 00:26:29,818
drove away all her painful memories
and her fond ones too.

355
00:26:29,902 --> 00:26:32,946
They say the human brain
shuts down when the pain is too much.

356
00:26:33,030 --> 00:26:34,239
I guess that's what happened?

357
00:26:34,323 --> 00:26:36,909
She endured until the breaking point came.

358
00:26:37,993 --> 00:26:40,913
Even so, she should not have lost herself.

359
00:26:42,206 --> 00:26:46,501
She needs to realize
that hollow peace is nothing but a prison.

360
00:26:46,585 --> 00:26:48,629
What a profound story.

361
00:26:49,129 --> 00:26:52,716
But, ma'am, when do you think
I'll land a lead role?

362
00:26:52,799 --> 00:26:55,093
There's a time for everything.

363
00:26:55,177 --> 00:26:56,887
<i>When the time comes,</i>

364
00:26:56,970 --> 00:26:59,514
<i>whether to move forward or to stay…</i>

365
00:27:01,225 --> 00:27:02,768
<i>the answer will reveal itself.</i>

366
00:27:20,869 --> 00:27:22,246
Why isn't she waking up?

367
00:27:22,329 --> 00:27:23,705
She doesn't even have any injuries.

368
00:27:23,789 --> 00:27:25,999
This can happen
even without any physical trauma.

369
00:27:26,083 --> 00:27:28,043
When the brain receives
a shock it cannot handle,

370
00:27:28,126 --> 00:27:30,128
it shuts down consciousness
to protect itself.

371
00:27:30,212 --> 00:27:32,089
A kind of escape mechanism, if you will.

372
00:27:32,172 --> 00:27:33,382
Then what should I do?

373
00:27:34,758 --> 00:27:36,385
I'm willing to try anything.

374
00:27:36,468 --> 00:27:38,345
Just stay by her side and talk to her.

375
00:27:38,971 --> 00:27:41,682
There's always a chance she can hear you.

376
00:27:51,566 --> 00:27:54,403
<i>Mr. Cha has had no recent contact</i>
<i>with the rest of the family.</i>

377
00:27:54,486 --> 00:27:57,781
His movements have been limited
to the office and the hospital.

378
00:27:57,864 --> 00:27:59,908
The hospital? You mean that woman?

379
00:27:59,992 --> 00:28:02,869
Yes, she's in a coma.

380
00:28:04,663 --> 00:28:08,333
Keep monitoring Cha Se-gye
until the press conference.

381
00:28:10,043 --> 00:28:12,421
Report any unusual movements in real time.

382
00:28:15,173 --> 00:28:18,510
Life's really put you through
the wringer and then some.

383
00:28:18,593 --> 00:28:21,471
Is your life just one big obstacle course
or something?

384
00:28:26,727 --> 00:28:28,103
Yes, Ms. Hong.

385
00:28:28,186 --> 00:28:30,230
Me? Where else would I be?

386
00:28:31,481 --> 00:28:32,649
I'm at home.

387
00:28:32,733 --> 00:28:34,860
How's the lawsuit
against the trolls going?

388
00:28:36,737 --> 00:28:38,322
I won't show them any leniency.

389
00:28:38,864 --> 00:28:39,948
Bye.

390
00:28:51,418 --> 00:28:52,419
Hello.

391
00:28:52,919 --> 00:28:54,129
Yeah, hi.

392
00:28:55,672 --> 00:28:56,798
Have you quit yet?

393
00:28:56,882 --> 00:28:58,675
Well, not yet, but I will.

394
00:28:58,759 --> 00:29:02,679
Still, the courteous thing to do would be
to say goodbye to Ms. Hong in person.

395
00:29:03,430 --> 00:29:04,473
Courteous? Yeah, right.

396
00:29:04,556 --> 00:29:06,850
Anyway, you made the right choice.

397
00:29:06,933 --> 00:29:09,853
No matter how I look at it, Mr. Baek,

398
00:29:09,936 --> 00:29:11,605
you're just not cut out to be a manager.

399
00:29:11,688 --> 00:29:13,023
Go find your true calling.

400
00:29:19,738 --> 00:29:21,114
I must have been blind.

401
00:29:21,698 --> 00:29:23,533
What did I ever see in that woman?

402
00:29:26,119 --> 00:29:27,913
SHIN SEO-RI

403
00:29:39,424 --> 00:29:42,010
Sir, you have a guest.

404
00:29:42,844 --> 00:29:45,722
She said she had something
to tell you regarding Ms. Shin.

405
00:29:48,725 --> 00:29:49,684
I see.

406
00:30:04,366 --> 00:30:06,535
To tell you the truth,

407
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,162
I have been channeling a spirit recently.

408
00:30:09,246 --> 00:30:11,123
When I finally came to, I was in a haze.

409
00:30:11,206 --> 00:30:13,250
I couldn't tell what was real
and what wasn't.

410
00:30:13,333 --> 00:30:14,292
I went to her place,

411
00:30:14,376 --> 00:30:17,295
and they told me she hasn't woken up yet.

412
00:30:17,379 --> 00:30:21,258
But I still felt like I had to come
and at least say something to you.

413
00:30:21,341 --> 00:30:24,219
I don't know
what con you're trying to pull,

414
00:30:25,137 --> 00:30:27,097
but you should get lost
while I'm still being nice.

415
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,265
Before I call the cops.

416
00:30:28,348 --> 00:30:30,392
Please don't be mad. Just hear me out.

417
00:30:30,475 --> 00:30:33,228
Even if no one else knows, you should.

418
00:30:33,311 --> 00:30:35,397
Seo-ri went to save you.

419
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,607
To save your life.

420
00:30:37,691 --> 00:30:39,985
She gave up everything and went back.

421
00:30:40,068 --> 00:30:41,069
Get out.

422
00:30:41,903 --> 00:30:42,904
Get out.

423
00:30:43,697 --> 00:30:44,823
Right now.

424
00:30:47,784 --> 00:30:49,870
Oh, gosh…

425
00:31:04,718 --> 00:31:07,804
<i>Even if the whole world</i>
<i>doesn't know it, you should.</i>

426
00:31:07,888 --> 00:31:10,182
<i>Seo-ri went to save you.</i>

427
00:31:11,016 --> 00:31:12,017
What a load of crap.

428
00:31:12,684 --> 00:31:14,519
<i>To save your life.</i>

429
00:31:14,603 --> 00:31:17,606
<i>She gave up everything and went back.</i>

430
00:31:44,883 --> 00:31:46,676
<i>Listen, Cha Se-gye.</i>

431
00:31:47,427 --> 00:31:49,429
<i>When spring comes,</i>

432
00:31:49,513 --> 00:31:51,723
<i>we should go see</i>
<i>the cornelian cherry flowers.</i>

433
00:31:51,806 --> 00:31:54,142
<i>We can make flower pancakes</i>
<i>with the yellow petals.</i>

434
00:31:54,226 --> 00:31:56,770
<i>In summer, we can enjoy</i>
<i>a yard spilling over with trumpet vines</i>

435
00:31:56,853 --> 00:31:58,855
<i>with peaches in our mouths.</i>

436
00:31:58,939 --> 00:32:02,067
<i>Or we can even go back to the sea</i>
<i>to look at the beach roses.</i>

437
00:32:02,651 --> 00:32:05,862
<i>And in autumn, make me</i>
<i>a crown of chrysanthemum blossoms.</i>

438
00:32:06,446 --> 00:32:09,282
<i>We can also go see</i>
<i>the autumn leaves while holding hands.</i>

439
00:32:09,783 --> 00:32:12,786
<i>Let us spend</i>
<i>all four seasons together like that.</i>

440
00:32:22,837 --> 00:32:23,922
Shin Seo-ri.

441
00:33:17,017 --> 00:33:17,976
How long

442
00:33:18,602 --> 00:33:20,478
has this been here?

443
00:33:29,279 --> 00:33:32,449
Mochang Group's new cosmetics line
managed to hit number one

444
00:33:32,532 --> 00:33:35,201
in Eastern Europe. Sorry, Se-gye.

445
00:33:37,037 --> 00:33:38,079
Se-gye.

446
00:33:39,998 --> 00:33:40,999
Se-gye?

447
00:33:44,502 --> 00:33:48,006
My apologies.
I didn't sleep well last night.

448
00:33:49,257 --> 00:33:50,592
Please continue.

449
00:33:51,843 --> 00:33:54,054
Is Ms. Shin still the same?

450
00:33:57,223 --> 00:33:59,809
Isn't it hard to keep waiting?

451
00:33:59,893 --> 00:34:01,519
Not knowing when she'll wake up

452
00:34:02,062 --> 00:34:04,898
or if she'll even get better.

453
00:34:08,777 --> 00:34:10,862
Please don't take this the wrong way.

454
00:34:11,529 --> 00:34:13,239
I'm just saying this out of concern.

455
00:34:16,451 --> 00:34:18,119
Waiting without an end in sight

456
00:34:19,621 --> 00:34:21,289
drains the life out of you.

457
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:25,210
And waiting doesn't guarantee
the answer you're hoping for.

458
00:34:37,555 --> 00:34:38,807
Se-gye.

459
00:34:39,599 --> 00:34:41,935
Have you ever been
to the museum across the street?

460
00:34:43,687 --> 00:34:45,730
They have an interesting painting there.

461
00:34:47,148 --> 00:34:49,567
A buyer who stopped by recently
was really taken with it.

462
00:34:49,651 --> 00:34:52,445
She said the painting looked like
it had a story behind it.

463
00:34:52,987 --> 00:34:55,824
It's half burned,
but it's a painting of a court lady.

464
00:34:56,658 --> 00:34:59,285
She looked like someone I know.

465
00:35:00,995 --> 00:35:03,998
<i>She bears a strong resemblance</i>
<i>to Ms. Shin.</i>

466
00:35:04,958 --> 00:35:06,584
<i>The court lady in that painting.</i>

467
00:35:09,087 --> 00:35:10,922
Could this be a brine stone?

468
00:35:15,844 --> 00:35:18,012
But I have never been to the sea.

469
00:35:23,935 --> 00:35:25,729
It looks like an ordinary painting,

470
00:35:25,812 --> 00:35:28,815
but this painting holds two secrets.

471
00:35:28,898 --> 00:35:29,983
In the Joseon era,

472
00:35:30,066 --> 00:35:33,445
it was rare for a woman's face
to be preserved in a portrait.

473
00:35:33,528 --> 00:35:37,240
This was due to the Confucian belief
in the separation of men and women.

474
00:35:37,323 --> 00:35:38,992
So, this painting

475
00:35:39,617 --> 00:35:41,661
must have been done in secret.

476
00:35:43,413 --> 00:35:46,541
<i>It was a bit unreal.</i>
<i>She could be her doppelgänger.</i>

477
00:35:47,250 --> 00:35:49,586
Do you see this book at the bottom?

478
00:35:49,669 --> 00:35:53,006
It is the <i>Seonghyeon Pavilion Diary,</i>
and it once belonged

479
00:35:53,089 --> 00:35:55,592
to Grand Prince Cheongheon,
Anjong's brother.

480
00:35:55,675 --> 00:36:00,263
The ill-fated prince who vanished in exile
after being swept up in a scandal.

481
00:36:00,346 --> 00:36:02,265
When it came back to Korea
just a year ago,

482
00:36:02,348 --> 00:36:04,768
no one expected it
to become this well-known.

483
00:36:04,851 --> 00:36:07,854
History is written
by the victors, after all.

484
00:36:07,937 --> 00:36:09,731
The page it is opened to

485
00:36:09,814 --> 00:36:13,693
is the last record Prince Cheongheon left
before his disappearance.

486
00:36:13,777 --> 00:36:16,654
It holds the truth, not the history
recorded in the royal Annals.

487
00:36:16,738 --> 00:36:19,699
"A Record of the Jeongchuk Day
of the Tenth Month, Byeongo Year."

488
00:36:19,783 --> 00:36:23,036
"The downpour that rattled the roof
through the night has ceased."

489
00:36:23,745 --> 00:36:26,456
<i>I used the collected rainwater</i>

490
00:36:27,207 --> 00:36:29,918
<i>to tidy myself up early in the morning.</i>

491
00:36:31,085 --> 00:36:32,754
<i>Today is different from yesterday.</i>

492
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:36,090
<i>She is coming here.</i>

493
00:36:51,356 --> 00:36:52,941
Are you on your way?

494
00:36:54,067 --> 00:36:55,109
To me?

495
00:36:58,571 --> 00:37:01,074
<i>I sought to rid my mind of you.</i>

496
00:37:01,825 --> 00:37:03,993
<i>Why are you coming to me now?</i>

497
00:37:04,619 --> 00:37:06,746
<i>Rather than aching with longing,</i>

498
00:37:06,830 --> 00:37:09,833
<i>hating me would serve your life better.</i>

499
00:37:11,501 --> 00:37:13,419
<i>I must drive you away with cruel words.</i>

500
00:37:14,379 --> 00:37:16,339
<i>Even if it breaks your heart,</i>

501
00:37:17,590 --> 00:37:19,634
<i>that is the way to save you.</i>

502
00:37:19,717 --> 00:37:20,593
<i>Bait?</i>

503
00:37:20,677 --> 00:37:22,303
Who do you think you are?

504
00:37:22,929 --> 00:37:24,973
Just because we shared
some banter as "companions,"

505
00:37:25,056 --> 00:37:27,559
do you truly think
that makes you something to me?

506
00:37:28,059 --> 00:37:29,310
I was happy.

507
00:37:29,811 --> 00:37:31,145
<i>I was just a court lady</i>

508
00:37:31,855 --> 00:37:34,274
<i>with no one to confide in but a stray dog.</i>

509
00:37:34,357 --> 00:37:37,110
I was happy when you offered
to be my companion.

510
00:37:42,156 --> 00:37:43,199
Shin Seo-ri.

511
00:37:44,117 --> 00:37:47,287
<i>Even if this is the end,</i>
<i>I cannot say it was a bad life.</i>

512
00:37:47,370 --> 00:37:50,456
<i>A royal who could never be sovereign.</i>

513
00:37:51,374 --> 00:37:54,002
<i>I was never destined</i>
<i>to live out a full life.</i>

514
00:37:54,085 --> 00:37:57,338
<i>Still, departing this life with the one</i>
<i>I treasure most kept safe…</i>

515
00:37:57,422 --> 00:37:59,674
<i>Is that not a rather</i>
<i>fitting end for a man?</i>

516
00:38:01,926 --> 00:38:04,095
<i>You must not drink that. It is poison!</i>

517
00:38:05,471 --> 00:38:07,682
<i>To save your life.</i>

518
00:38:07,765 --> 00:38:10,435
<i>She gave up everything and went back.</i>

519
00:38:10,518 --> 00:38:13,021
<i>Did I not tell you?</i>
<i>I am trying to save you.</i>

520
00:38:13,605 --> 00:38:15,857
<i>He </i>will only live
if Your Highness survives.

521
00:38:18,443 --> 00:38:21,279
<i>He is more precious than life to me.</i>

522
00:38:42,258 --> 00:38:43,301
<i>Can't we</i>

523
00:38:44,510 --> 00:38:45,678
<i>just stop all this now?</i>

524
00:38:54,771 --> 00:38:56,356
Wow, it's snowing!

525
00:38:56,439 --> 00:38:58,483
Mom, look! It's snow.

526
00:38:58,566 --> 00:39:00,318
Snow in the middle of summer?

527
00:39:01,194 --> 00:39:02,737
What deep sorrow brought this on?

528
00:39:02,820 --> 00:39:04,489
More like freak weather.

529
00:39:04,572 --> 00:39:06,199
It's still pretty though.

530
00:39:07,283 --> 00:39:10,912
EMBRACING JOSEON ONCE MORE

531
00:39:24,258 --> 00:39:26,552
Can't you please stop making me wait?

532
00:39:30,056 --> 00:39:31,057
<i>I…</i>

533
00:39:32,767 --> 00:39:34,894
<i>can't breathe, Shin Seo-ri.</i>

534
00:39:38,022 --> 00:39:39,273
<i>Come back.</i>

535
00:39:40,024 --> 00:39:41,067
<i>Please…</i>

536
00:40:03,256 --> 00:40:04,590
He is alive.

537
00:40:08,052 --> 00:40:09,429
<i>Shin Seo-ri, look at me.</i>

538
00:40:09,512 --> 00:40:10,847
<i>I'm right here.</i>

539
00:40:10,930 --> 00:40:12,181
<i>Cha Se-gye.</i>

540
00:40:15,309 --> 00:40:17,228
<i>No matter how dark the night is,</i>

541
00:40:17,311 --> 00:40:18,813
<i>if someone is by your side,</i>

542
00:40:18,896 --> 00:40:21,232
<i>it is a bit more bearable and less scary.</i>

543
00:40:21,816 --> 00:40:23,276
<i>It is not about where you are.</i>

544
00:40:23,359 --> 00:40:25,945
<i>It is about who you are with.</i>

545
00:40:29,657 --> 00:40:31,576
I harbor affection for you.

546
00:40:31,659 --> 00:40:32,869
I just need you.

547
00:40:32,952 --> 00:40:34,912
You're the only one, Shin Seo-ri.

548
00:40:34,996 --> 00:40:36,456
Let me be your only one too.

549
00:40:38,791 --> 00:40:39,917
<i>Cha Se-gye.</i>

550
00:40:40,460 --> 00:40:43,087
<i>No matter what happens</i>
<i>to us in the future,</i>

551
00:40:43,171 --> 00:40:46,382
<i>just remember</i>
<i>that I truly hold you in my heart.</i>

552
00:40:46,466 --> 00:40:48,134
<i>I will take that with me wherever I go.</i>

553
00:40:48,217 --> 00:40:51,387
<i>And with that one memory,</i>
<i>I will flourish and not wither away.</i>

554
00:40:51,471 --> 00:40:52,805
<i>Promise me.</i>

555
00:40:54,182 --> 00:40:56,559
<i>I will make sure you are not alone.</i>

556
00:40:57,101 --> 00:40:58,227
<i>You can trust me.</i>

557
00:40:58,811 --> 00:41:00,772
<i>Don't forget that promise, Shin Seo-ri.</i>

558
00:41:06,652 --> 00:41:10,364
<i>Protecting you. I gave you my word.</i>

559
00:41:13,576 --> 00:41:15,036
<i>Your punishment has ended.</i>

560
00:41:15,119 --> 00:41:17,205
<i>Now, you may be free from your pain.</i>

561
00:41:18,122 --> 00:41:19,123
No.

562
00:41:19,207 --> 00:41:23,044
<i>Sever every knotted thread of connection,</i>
<i>whether ill-fated or destined.</i>

563
00:41:23,127 --> 00:41:25,421
<i>Then you shall never again lose</i>
<i>the ones you hold dear</i>

564
00:41:25,505 --> 00:41:27,965
<i>or shed another tear for them.</i>

565
00:41:28,049 --> 00:41:29,050
No.

566
00:41:29,133 --> 00:41:32,053
<i>This is a reward</i>
<i>bestowed upon you by the heavens.</i>

567
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:33,721
This is no reward.

568
00:41:33,805 --> 00:41:35,973
Without pain, there is no happiness.

569
00:41:37,558 --> 00:41:40,144
Without sorrow, you cannot feel joy.

570
00:41:40,853 --> 00:41:42,772
I have no need for such a reward.

571
00:41:46,526 --> 00:41:50,154
Then I shall give you
one last chance to choose.

572
00:41:50,238 --> 00:41:52,281
You may go anywhere.

573
00:41:52,365 --> 00:41:54,826
The past or the present.

574
00:41:55,326 --> 00:41:58,079
Even the future or another world.

575
00:42:00,456 --> 00:42:04,127
You can even go to a world
where you bear no trace of the vixen.

576
00:42:06,129 --> 00:42:08,297
Where will you head to?

577
00:42:09,048 --> 00:42:11,134
I have already made my decision.

578
00:42:11,926 --> 00:42:13,094
I choose…

579
00:42:47,295 --> 00:42:48,171
Cha Se-gye.

580
00:43:24,498 --> 00:43:25,958
It is snowing.

581
00:43:27,418 --> 00:43:29,629
Why are you out here getting snowed on?

582
00:43:38,346 --> 00:43:39,555
You…

583
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:48,981
I missed you.

584
00:43:50,691 --> 00:43:51,943
So much.

585
00:44:22,223 --> 00:44:24,058
I am so glad you are alive.

586
00:44:25,559 --> 00:44:27,395
Thank you for staying alive.

587
00:44:30,648 --> 00:44:31,607
You.

588
00:44:33,818 --> 00:44:35,152
How could you?

589
00:44:38,364 --> 00:44:40,241
How could you leave me behind?

590
00:44:41,117 --> 00:44:43,411
How was I supposed to live without you?

591
00:44:43,494 --> 00:44:45,579
But I am here now.

592
00:44:46,372 --> 00:44:47,832
Both of us are here

593
00:44:48,958 --> 00:44:50,793
perfectly alive.

594
00:44:52,878 --> 00:44:55,172
I really thought you were dying.

595
00:44:56,590 --> 00:44:58,467
I almost died waiting for you.

596
00:45:00,136 --> 00:45:02,013
I never even told you
how I feel about you.

597
00:45:03,014 --> 00:45:05,057
I never had a chance
to tell you I love you.

598
00:45:05,141 --> 00:45:07,101
How could you just leave like that?

599
00:45:12,648 --> 00:45:13,941
You can do it now.

600
00:45:14,900 --> 00:45:16,319
You can do it every day.

601
00:45:18,446 --> 00:45:20,823
I love you, Cha Se-gye.

602
00:45:29,582 --> 00:45:31,625
Look at you, beating me to it again.

603
00:45:33,002 --> 00:45:34,420
You're seriously…

604
00:45:35,671 --> 00:45:37,173
You and me for the next hundred years.

605
00:45:37,256 --> 00:45:38,466
A hundred years?

606
00:45:39,550 --> 00:45:41,260
I want a thousand. Ten thousand.

607
00:45:41,344 --> 00:45:42,845
You're not going anywhere now.

608
00:45:44,638 --> 00:45:45,765
Fine.

609
00:45:45,848 --> 00:45:47,058
Deal sealed.

610
00:46:27,181 --> 00:46:28,682
Shin Seo-ri, slap me.

611
00:46:28,766 --> 00:46:29,934
Slap you?

612
00:46:31,143 --> 00:46:33,062
We reunite, and that is what you want?

613
00:46:33,145 --> 00:46:34,397
It just doesn't feel real.

614
00:46:34,480 --> 00:46:35,981
I think I might be dreaming.

615
00:46:36,065 --> 00:46:37,900
So hit me hard.

616
00:46:45,199 --> 00:46:47,410
This is not a dream. This is real.

617
00:46:48,202 --> 00:46:49,787
How is it? Nice and warm?

618
00:46:50,413 --> 00:46:51,372
Yeah.

619
00:46:53,666 --> 00:46:54,917
It's nice and warm.

620
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:56,919
You really are the Shin Seo-ri I know.

621
00:46:57,545 --> 00:46:58,546
Unbelievable.

622
00:46:59,797 --> 00:47:02,425
What took you so long?
Were you trying to torture me?

623
00:47:04,260 --> 00:47:06,178
I thought you were dead.

624
00:47:08,180 --> 00:47:11,267
"In the end, I could not save one.
I am the sole survivor."

625
00:47:11,350 --> 00:47:12,601
"And now,

626
00:47:13,602 --> 00:47:15,563
I truly have no one left."

627
00:47:18,274 --> 00:47:20,192
But then I heard your voice.

628
00:47:22,820 --> 00:47:24,738
In a place with no day or night,

629
00:47:25,656 --> 00:47:27,283
your voice was clear as the sun.

630
00:47:29,577 --> 00:47:32,496
You saved me, Cha Se-gye.

631
00:47:33,038 --> 00:47:34,540
You pulled me out of there.

632
00:47:35,833 --> 00:47:37,251
No, you saved me.

633
00:47:37,877 --> 00:47:39,879
Both of us.

634
00:47:42,715 --> 00:47:43,716
And him too.

635
00:47:45,759 --> 00:47:48,554
The fact that I'm right here
in front of you is proof.

636
00:47:50,222 --> 00:47:51,432
That we are alive.

637
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:02,109
<i>They must be finding their way</i>
<i>along their own path.</i>

638
00:48:03,944 --> 00:48:05,696
<i>Looking completely different.</i>

639
00:48:09,909 --> 00:48:11,660
You are not a boy. You are a girl.

640
00:48:15,581 --> 00:48:16,499
That's a secret, kiddo.

641
00:48:17,249 --> 00:48:18,167
Here.

642
00:48:20,628 --> 00:48:22,213
What is your name?

643
00:48:22,296 --> 00:48:24,757
My name is Dan-sim.

644
00:48:25,674 --> 00:48:26,550
Kang Dan-sim.

645
00:48:30,554 --> 00:48:31,847
Halt.

646
00:48:34,266 --> 00:48:35,267
A composite sketch!

647
00:48:37,019 --> 00:48:38,312
A comp-what now?

648
00:48:46,487 --> 00:48:49,490
Hey, Park.
You should be carrying our bundles.

649
00:48:49,573 --> 00:48:51,909
The ferry to Qing is that way.

650
00:48:57,206 --> 00:48:59,708
You are forgetful.
I should have been more attentive.

651
00:49:00,209 --> 00:49:01,168
It's fine.

652
00:49:01,710 --> 00:49:03,504
Let's ditch those cops and run.

653
00:49:04,171 --> 00:49:05,089
You really are

654
00:49:05,923 --> 00:49:07,299
like a different person.

655
00:49:07,383 --> 00:49:08,884
From your speech to your eyes.

656
00:49:08,968 --> 00:49:11,428
I told you. I made a comeback
to my own body.

657
00:49:11,512 --> 00:49:13,681
Anyway, let's scram. That way.

658
00:49:15,724 --> 00:49:16,767
All right.

659
00:49:17,893 --> 00:49:19,311
Let us scram, then. Quickly.

660
00:49:19,937 --> 00:49:21,188
Bye!

661
00:49:23,357 --> 00:49:25,317
<i>They're probably out there living it up</i>

662
00:49:25,985 --> 00:49:27,403
<i>somewhere we'll never know.</i>

663
00:49:28,028 --> 00:49:29,321
<i>I'm sure of it.</i>

664
00:49:30,281 --> 00:49:31,824
I want to believe that.

665
00:49:31,907 --> 00:49:34,535
Things never went the way I believed.

666
00:49:35,035 --> 00:49:36,203
But I want to believe that.

667
00:49:36,287 --> 00:49:37,746
I'm telling you I'm right.

668
00:49:38,914 --> 00:49:40,124
I can guarantee it.

669
00:49:40,624 --> 00:49:42,543
Okay. I will believe it.

670
00:49:43,335 --> 00:49:45,546
Up until now,
I was busy scrambling to survive.

671
00:49:45,629 --> 00:49:47,840
Now I want to live the way I believe.

672
00:49:47,923 --> 00:49:48,924
Good.

673
00:49:49,675 --> 00:49:51,302
Let's turn over a new leaf too.

674
00:49:51,385 --> 00:49:54,388
No more giving people ammunition.
Let's just be good and kind.

675
00:49:54,471 --> 00:49:56,140
No. We cannot do that.

676
00:49:57,266 --> 00:50:00,019
Why be nice in this cruel world?
Want to be a pushover?

677
00:50:00,102 --> 00:50:02,104
If someone betrays you,
you hunt them down.

678
00:50:02,187 --> 00:50:03,939
Anyone who badmouths you
gets it back double.

679
00:50:04,023 --> 00:50:05,357
We must be ruthless.

680
00:50:05,983 --> 00:50:07,276
Wait, why?

681
00:50:07,359 --> 00:50:09,695
Why are you so fired up?
Even more intense than before.

682
00:50:09,778 --> 00:50:12,489
Turning over a new leaf too quickly
can be lethal.

683
00:50:12,573 --> 00:50:14,283
After everything I did
to make it back alive?

684
00:50:14,366 --> 00:50:16,285
I shall outlive them all.

685
00:50:16,827 --> 00:50:18,037
In that spirit…

686
00:50:19,955 --> 00:50:23,250
we cannot just let everything end
on good terms like this.

687
00:50:27,087 --> 00:50:29,298
What's with that look? It's scary.

688
00:50:30,591 --> 00:50:32,509
The reporters have arrived.

689
00:50:32,593 --> 00:50:34,637
I'll be leaving
for the US branch right after this,

690
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:36,138
so go and pick up Seo-jun.

691
00:50:37,097 --> 00:50:39,808
Until now, Chail deserved
every bit of criticism

692
00:50:39,892 --> 00:50:42,561
for its incompetence, greed,
and the resulting scandals.

693
00:50:42,645 --> 00:50:43,729
Times like these

694
00:50:43,812 --> 00:50:47,358
call for decisive action
to carve out what's rotten.

695
00:50:47,441 --> 00:50:50,944
Let me make this clear to all of you now.

696
00:50:51,445 --> 00:50:53,197
Should further police investigation
be needed,

697
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:55,658
we shall continue to comply diligently

698
00:50:55,741 --> 00:50:57,910
and maintain full transparency

699
00:50:57,993 --> 00:50:59,870
until the full truth is revealed.

700
00:50:59,953 --> 00:51:03,082
Is that to say you had no part
in any of these matters?

701
00:51:03,165 --> 00:51:05,834
Legally, I may have no involvement,

702
00:51:07,252 --> 00:51:09,004
but as family,
I feel very much responsible.

703
00:51:09,088 --> 00:51:12,299
You cleverly sidestepped
the allegations made against you directly.

704
00:51:12,383 --> 00:51:14,218
Is that the purpose
of today's press conference?

705
00:51:14,301 --> 00:51:15,552
Which outlet are you from?

706
00:51:15,636 --> 00:51:16,887
Please state your affiliation.

707
00:51:19,556 --> 00:51:20,474
Affiliation?

708
00:51:27,606 --> 00:51:29,233
I am affiliated with Cha Se-gye.

709
00:51:30,859 --> 00:51:33,070
You dared to mess with my man.

710
00:51:34,863 --> 00:51:36,824
You are dead meat today.

711
00:51:36,907 --> 00:51:37,991
Get rid of her.

712
00:51:43,455 --> 00:51:44,915
Stand back, you scoundrels!

713
00:51:44,998 --> 00:51:46,917
Before I snap your wrists in half.

714
00:51:56,969 --> 00:51:59,221
You should've left her alone
when she said so.

715
00:51:59,304 --> 00:52:01,098
Now your wrists are broken for nothing.

716
00:52:01,181 --> 00:52:03,100
What took you so long?
You should have run over.

717
00:52:03,183 --> 00:52:04,476
Traffic was bad. What could I do?

718
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:06,520
Traffic in Seoul is a serious problem.

719
00:52:06,603 --> 00:52:08,439
What do you think you're doing?

720
00:52:08,981 --> 00:52:10,607
This is a press conference.

721
00:52:10,691 --> 00:52:11,650
Yeah.

722
00:52:11,734 --> 00:52:13,610
Just looking to have
some fun with the reporters.

723
00:52:13,694 --> 00:52:14,862
Mr. Son.

724
00:52:16,321 --> 00:52:18,115
RE: CHOI MUN-DO ABANDONS BODY

725
00:52:18,198 --> 00:52:20,909
Can I ask all the reporters here
to check their phones?

726
00:52:23,495 --> 00:52:24,580
-What is this?
-Hold on.

727
00:52:52,649 --> 00:52:53,776
Cha Se-gye.

728
00:52:55,277 --> 00:52:56,236
What is this?

729
00:52:57,237 --> 00:52:58,155
Right.

730
00:52:58,739 --> 00:53:01,658
I acquired them the day
you spread that power-trip video.

731
00:53:04,328 --> 00:53:05,746
My word.

732
00:53:05,829 --> 00:53:08,415
Their deepfake work
has improved again since then.

733
00:53:08,499 --> 00:53:09,917
Looks real, doesn't it?

734
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:11,043
It really does.

735
00:53:12,044 --> 00:53:13,545
It really is a scary world.

736
00:53:13,629 --> 00:53:16,256
I suppose you could call this foresight?

737
00:53:22,679 --> 00:53:23,555
30 MINUTES AGO

738
00:53:23,639 --> 00:53:25,557
Our job is to represent
the company's interests.

739
00:53:25,641 --> 00:53:28,435
Whether this benefits
or harms the company.

740
00:53:28,519 --> 00:53:31,688
Let that be your guiding principle
as you cast your votes.

741
00:53:31,772 --> 00:53:33,690
<i>Effective immediately,</i>
<i>Choi Mun-do is no longer</i>

742
00:53:33,774 --> 00:53:36,485
<i>the interim chairman of Chail Group.</i>
<i>He is just a private citizen now.</i>

743
00:53:36,568 --> 00:53:38,445
You have been notified
by the board of directors

744
00:53:38,529 --> 00:53:41,073
of your dismissal
from the interim CEO position.

745
00:53:41,156 --> 00:53:44,159
Naturally, your trial
will not be handled by Chail's legal team.

746
00:53:44,243 --> 00:53:45,953
Who says there's going to be a trial?

747
00:53:46,036 --> 00:53:47,538
Can't make an arrest without evidence.

748
00:53:47,621 --> 00:53:49,039
There certainly is evidence.

749
00:53:52,835 --> 00:53:53,961
Mr. Choi Mun-do.

750
00:53:55,128 --> 00:53:57,047
Please come with us. You're under arrest.

751
00:53:57,130 --> 00:53:59,967
This must be about the illegal video.
But it's a deepfake.

752
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:02,761
The police wouldn't move
this swiftly over a fabricated video.

753
00:54:02,845 --> 00:54:04,263
Isn't that right, Inspector Lee?

754
00:54:04,346 --> 00:54:06,723
Yes, your aide turned himself in.

755
00:54:06,807 --> 00:54:08,559
It appears he recorded

756
00:54:08,642 --> 00:54:11,061
and documented every task
you've ever given him.

757
00:54:11,144 --> 00:54:13,063
The statements alone could fill a truck.

758
00:54:13,146 --> 00:54:14,273
Such is life.

759
00:54:14,356 --> 00:54:16,859
You should have hired better subordinates.

760
00:54:16,942 --> 00:54:18,986
No. When the water upstream is dirty,

761
00:54:19,069 --> 00:54:20,988
the water downstream cannot run clear.

762
00:54:34,376 --> 00:54:36,086
Why are you so lost in thought?

763
00:54:36,169 --> 00:54:37,838
This is the problem with the 21st century.

764
00:54:37,921 --> 00:54:40,716
When you cannot deliver justice yourself,
it never quite satisfies.

765
00:54:40,799 --> 00:54:43,176
It wouldn't be
the 21st century if we could.

766
00:54:43,260 --> 00:54:46,847
What kind of Stone Age society
has you getting blood on your hands?

767
00:54:46,930 --> 00:54:48,098
This will not do.

768
00:54:48,181 --> 00:54:50,183
Any karma I can exact myself,

769
00:54:50,684 --> 00:54:52,519
I shall make sure it is thorough.

770
00:54:53,186 --> 00:54:54,104
Oh my God!

771
00:54:54,187 --> 00:54:56,440
Who the hell left this here?

772
00:54:57,399 --> 00:54:58,442
Damn it.

773
00:55:02,070 --> 00:55:03,155
What the…

774
00:55:03,655 --> 00:55:04,698
<i>Reflect.</i>

775
00:55:06,408 --> 00:55:07,951
Shin Seo-ri, you crazy…

776
00:55:09,369 --> 00:55:10,871
Damn it.

777
00:55:10,954 --> 00:55:12,331
<i>Right back at you, punk.</i>

778
00:55:12,414 --> 00:55:15,042
<i>Royal Consort Kang,</i>
<i>the villainess with the poison refills?</i>

779
00:55:15,125 --> 00:55:16,084
<i>Here is the real tea.</i>

780
00:55:16,168 --> 00:55:20,297
<i>Court intrigue? Just Anjong's gaslighting.</i>
<i>The consorts and the Queen were victims.</i>

781
00:55:20,380 --> 00:55:24,468
<i>Using women as shields for personal gain?</i>
<i>Posthumous decapitation is only fitting.</i>

782
00:55:26,094 --> 00:55:27,804
Perhaps that sounds too elegant?

783
00:55:32,142 --> 00:55:33,977
<i>Eradication is the answer.</i>

784
00:55:37,439 --> 00:55:38,523
Perfect.

785
00:55:40,317 --> 00:55:41,401
-Jeez!
-Any grievances?

786
00:55:41,485 --> 00:55:42,986
I can serve up some karma for you.

787
00:55:43,070 --> 00:55:45,656
Enough already.
There's just no middle ground with you.

788
00:55:47,699 --> 00:55:48,742
Ms. Hong.

789
00:55:48,825 --> 00:55:49,785
Hey,

790
00:55:49,868 --> 00:55:53,080
what kind of intern
submits their resignation offline?

791
00:55:53,163 --> 00:55:54,790
A phone call would've sufficed.

792
00:55:55,791 --> 00:55:56,833
I see.

793
00:55:58,043 --> 00:55:59,044
Gosh.

794
00:56:00,253 --> 00:56:01,546
Did you find a new manager?

795
00:56:01,630 --> 00:56:02,965
I need to hire one,

796
00:56:03,674 --> 00:56:04,549
but we're in trouble.

797
00:56:04,633 --> 00:56:07,761
Word of Ji-hyo's temper
has spread all over the industry.

798
00:56:07,844 --> 00:56:10,973
She's apparently number one
on the manager community blacklist.

799
00:56:12,307 --> 00:56:15,519
I'm pretty sure the troll responsible
is an industry insider too.

800
00:56:15,602 --> 00:56:18,313
What? And I'm a suspect now?

801
00:56:18,397 --> 00:56:22,317
No, I was just wondering
if you knew of any potential suspects.

802
00:56:23,276 --> 00:56:25,654
-It's not me.
-Right, it shouldn't be.

803
00:56:28,740 --> 00:56:30,993
With a mouth like hers,

804
00:56:31,076 --> 00:56:33,578
it was always
going to come back to bite her.

805
00:56:33,662 --> 00:56:35,747
How is there still no progress
on the troll lawsuit?

806
00:56:35,831 --> 00:56:36,873
Hey!

807
00:56:37,749 --> 00:56:38,959
Did you block my number?

808
00:56:39,042 --> 00:56:40,377
What the… Gong Tae-woo?

809
00:56:40,877 --> 00:56:42,754
What are you doing here?

810
00:56:44,172 --> 00:56:45,298
-Give it.
-Damn it.

811
00:56:45,382 --> 00:56:47,968
Give it back! Damn it.

812
00:56:48,051 --> 00:56:50,220
<i>The call cannot be connected…</i>

813
00:56:50,303 --> 00:56:51,513
You really did block me.

814
00:56:52,097 --> 00:56:54,349
Unblock me and drop the charges.

815
00:56:55,475 --> 00:56:59,312
We're broken up.
Why do you care if I block you or not?

816
00:57:01,606 --> 00:57:03,608
Wait, did you post hate comments about me?

817
00:57:03,692 --> 00:57:05,527
You petty bastard.

818
00:57:05,610 --> 00:57:08,447
No wonder there was always
a grain of truth buried in every post.

819
00:57:08,530 --> 00:57:09,656
I'll see you at the station.

820
00:57:09,740 --> 00:57:12,325
Get ready to be completely
and utterly humiliated.

821
00:57:12,868 --> 00:57:14,036
Hey, Yoon Ji-hyo!

822
00:57:14,119 --> 00:57:15,287
Damn it. Let go!

823
00:57:15,370 --> 00:57:17,539
-Let me go!
-Knock it off!

824
00:57:19,499 --> 00:57:21,501
I get that you're still not over me,

825
00:57:21,585 --> 00:57:24,212
but you can't just take a dump
all over someone's life like this.

826
00:57:24,296 --> 00:57:26,256
She's clearly not the one full of crap.

827
00:57:28,091 --> 00:57:29,009
Who are you?

828
00:57:44,858 --> 00:57:45,901
Let her go.

829
00:57:45,984 --> 00:57:47,903
Article 260,
Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act.

830
00:57:47,986 --> 00:57:49,529
Any person who assaults another

831
00:57:49,613 --> 00:57:51,573
shall be punished by
up to two years of imprisonment

832
00:57:51,656 --> 00:57:53,575
or a fine not exceeding 5 million won.

833
00:57:54,076 --> 00:57:55,285
What? Are you a lawyer?

834
00:57:55,368 --> 00:57:57,079
Me? I'm not a lawyer.

835
00:57:57,162 --> 00:57:58,288
Civil servant hopeful…

836
00:57:59,122 --> 00:58:00,582
turned manager. Why?

837
00:58:01,208 --> 00:58:03,126
This is all being recorded right now.

838
00:58:03,210 --> 00:58:05,087
Want me to take a video too?

839
00:58:05,170 --> 00:58:07,047
Should I go live
for the whole country to see?

840
00:58:07,130 --> 00:58:08,965
-Hey, don't film me! Don't.
-Should I?

841
00:58:09,049 --> 00:58:10,008
Hey.

842
00:58:10,926 --> 00:58:12,803
You better drop those charges.

843
00:58:12,886 --> 00:58:15,180
Article 283,
Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act.

844
00:58:15,263 --> 00:58:16,515
Any person who threatens another

845
00:58:16,598 --> 00:58:19,184
shall face up to 3 years of imprisonment
or a 5 million won fine.

846
00:58:19,267 --> 00:58:20,477
Damn it.

847
00:58:20,560 --> 00:58:22,229
What a bastard.

848
00:58:22,312 --> 00:58:23,688
What did I ever do to him

849
00:58:24,231 --> 00:58:26,525
to deserve this?

850
00:58:26,608 --> 00:58:27,818
What did I…

851
00:58:35,033 --> 00:58:36,368
Damn it.

852
00:58:38,328 --> 00:58:40,831
You did do something wrong.
You did indeed.

853
00:58:40,914 --> 00:58:42,582
Seriously? Damn it.

854
00:58:42,666 --> 00:58:45,794
It's wrong for you to look this pretty
even when you're crying.

855
00:58:46,962 --> 00:58:50,340
Disproportionate self pity.
I'd call that a crime too.

856
00:58:50,423 --> 00:58:54,427
So forget the hate comments
and all that other crap.

857
00:58:54,511 --> 00:58:56,138
And focus on yourself.

858
00:58:58,557 --> 00:59:00,892
Ji-hyo, you're a much better person

859
00:59:00,976 --> 00:59:02,394
than you think you are.

860
00:59:02,477 --> 00:59:04,479
Trust me. I'm a good judge of character.

861
00:59:07,315 --> 00:59:08,400
Need more?

862
00:59:11,111 --> 00:59:12,112
Here.

863
00:59:14,156 --> 00:59:16,158
Go on, wipe your tears.

864
00:59:37,179 --> 00:59:39,556
You came here alone without Se-gye?

865
00:59:41,057 --> 00:59:41,975
Before the trial.

866
00:59:42,475 --> 00:59:43,560
Right, that trial.

867
00:59:44,728 --> 00:59:46,730
People are lining up
to send you to your grave.

868
00:59:46,813 --> 00:59:49,482
Your aide, Director Jang,

869
00:59:49,566 --> 00:59:50,942
and even your staff at home.

870
00:59:51,026 --> 00:59:52,235
Just a line around the block.

871
00:59:53,945 --> 00:59:55,572
That won't work on me.

872
00:59:56,323 --> 00:59:58,325
I won't be in here for long.

873
00:59:58,909 --> 00:59:59,868
What do you want?

874
00:59:59,951 --> 01:00:00,911
Do you…

875
01:00:02,120 --> 01:00:03,288
believe in fate?

876
01:00:06,708 --> 01:00:07,584
Fate?

877
01:00:07,667 --> 01:00:10,587
That everything is
predetermined and unchanging.

878
01:00:10,670 --> 01:00:13,506
That nothing changes
no matter how hard you try.

879
01:00:13,590 --> 01:00:16,635
Therefore do not dare
to dishonor your betters,

880
01:00:18,053 --> 01:00:21,056
forget your station, or rise against them.

881
01:00:21,139 --> 01:00:22,807
It is quite a garbage notion.

882
01:00:23,391 --> 01:00:24,935
Created by those in power.

883
01:00:26,811 --> 01:00:28,688
I do not believe in fate anymore.

884
01:00:29,231 --> 01:00:33,109
Instead, I have come to believe
in the karma I have created.

885
01:00:33,193 --> 01:00:36,571
Because you and I are living proof of it.

886
01:00:38,490 --> 01:00:40,951
I was curious enough to come hear you out…

887
01:00:42,827 --> 01:00:45,705
but you should save
your half-baked philosophy for Se-gye.

888
01:00:46,248 --> 01:00:48,917
I can't listen to this anymore.

889
01:00:52,003 --> 01:00:54,172
You really are clueless.

890
01:00:55,257 --> 01:00:56,591
With such ignorance,

891
01:00:56,675 --> 01:00:59,970
you will rot away in this cold prison.

892
01:01:02,264 --> 01:01:06,226
After squandering your one chance
to rewrite your mistakes.

893
01:01:11,147 --> 01:01:13,400
Chance? What chance?

894
01:01:13,483 --> 01:01:16,695
The chance to save your corrupted soul.

895
01:01:17,320 --> 01:01:18,822
<i>Dad!</i>

896
01:01:19,656 --> 01:01:23,535
<i>The chance to wash away</i>
<i>the greed etched in your soul.</i>

897
01:01:23,618 --> 01:01:26,997
<i>Your one chance to become whole.</i>

898
01:01:27,080 --> 01:01:28,873
<i>You blew that chance.</i>

899
01:01:29,499 --> 01:01:32,502
You can now ruminate
on that chance you threw away

900
01:01:33,169 --> 01:01:34,838
in this cold prison

901
01:01:36,381 --> 01:01:37,716
for the rest of your life

902
01:01:38,258 --> 01:01:39,467
as it gnaws away at you

903
01:01:40,719 --> 01:01:41,928
bit by bit.

904
01:02:03,533 --> 01:02:04,534
Grandma.

905
01:02:06,244 --> 01:02:07,579
How is it up there?

906
01:02:07,662 --> 01:02:11,333
Are you resting well
in a warm, sunny house?

907
01:02:12,292 --> 01:02:13,918
I'm doing well too.

908
01:02:14,002 --> 01:02:14,961
REST IN PEACE NAM OK-SUN

909
01:02:15,045 --> 01:02:16,629
Finding small joys along the way

910
01:02:17,339 --> 01:02:19,382
with someone who stays by my side.

911
01:02:27,849 --> 01:02:29,142
So please watch over me.

912
01:02:30,226 --> 01:02:32,312
See how fully I live my life,

913
01:02:32,979 --> 01:02:35,357
making up for lost happiness
with interest,

914
01:02:36,524 --> 01:02:38,193
surrounded by warmth.

915
01:02:46,242 --> 01:02:48,953
<i>Fly freely, Seo-ri.</i>

916
01:02:54,709 --> 01:02:56,252
Jeez, did he call you again?

917
01:02:57,879 --> 01:03:00,548
Why does Grandfather
keep calling you instead of me?

918
01:03:01,424 --> 01:03:02,884
You should have answered his calls.

919
01:03:02,967 --> 01:03:04,761
He said he is about to block you

920
01:03:05,345 --> 01:03:06,763
because you never pick up.

921
01:03:06,846 --> 01:03:09,724
Block me? As if he could defy
the laws of parental love.

922
01:03:09,808 --> 01:03:11,893
It sounded like he was about to defy them.

923
01:03:12,644 --> 01:03:14,062
You will be hung out to dry.

924
01:03:17,607 --> 01:03:18,733
Why would I be hung out?

925
01:03:18,817 --> 01:03:19,943
Father,

926
01:03:20,026 --> 01:03:21,277
I've made my decision.

927
01:03:21,361 --> 01:03:22,612
I'm getting a divorce.

928
01:03:23,154 --> 01:03:24,531
I just submitted the papers.

929
01:03:24,614 --> 01:03:27,242
Yeah. Divorce isn't anything
to be ashamed of nowadays.

930
01:03:27,325 --> 01:03:28,993
Plenty of people do it two or three times.

931
01:03:29,077 --> 01:03:30,912
Nothing to brag about, either.

932
01:03:30,995 --> 01:03:34,541
Goodness, how did both my kids
end up divorced?

933
01:03:37,127 --> 01:03:38,086
Grandfather!

934
01:03:38,169 --> 01:03:39,754
Gosh. My sweet boy.

935
01:03:40,839 --> 01:03:43,049
There you are. Are you back from school?

936
01:03:43,133 --> 01:03:44,217
-Yes.
-Good.

937
01:03:44,300 --> 01:03:46,636
We played kickball in PE today,

938
01:03:46,719 --> 01:03:47,679
and my class won!

939
01:03:47,762 --> 01:03:50,348
Well done. Excellent.

940
01:03:50,432 --> 01:03:53,226
Wow, our Seo-jun is great at kickball too.

941
01:03:53,309 --> 01:03:54,644
You're good at every sport.

942
01:03:55,937 --> 01:03:56,980
Yeah.

943
01:03:58,148 --> 01:04:00,316
Since when is kickball a sport?

944
01:04:00,400 --> 01:04:03,445
What's so special about some kids
kicking around a little ball?

945
01:04:03,528 --> 01:04:05,613
If you're going to be like this,
don't bother coming.

946
01:04:05,697 --> 01:04:07,574
Why come here just to spoil the mood?

947
01:04:07,657 --> 01:04:08,616
Hey.

948
01:04:08,700 --> 01:04:11,744
I'm trying to start things off
on the right foot with him. What?

949
01:04:11,828 --> 01:04:13,329
You bitch even when I show up.

950
01:04:14,914 --> 01:04:16,040
"Bitch"?

951
01:04:17,542 --> 01:04:18,710
No.

952
01:04:18,793 --> 01:04:21,087
I meant, "hitch." Auntie misspoke.

953
01:04:21,171 --> 01:04:23,590
You see, a hitch is
like a hiccup that stops you

954
01:04:23,673 --> 01:04:25,467
and causes you to be late and stuff.

955
01:04:25,550 --> 01:04:27,635
I see. It makes you run late?

956
01:04:27,719 --> 01:04:28,970
Auntie, are you a hitcher?

957
01:04:29,053 --> 01:04:30,638
That's right, she's one big hitcher.

958
01:04:32,056 --> 01:04:33,600
-Hitcher.
-Hitcher…

959
01:04:33,683 --> 01:04:35,018
She's a hitcher all right.

960
01:04:41,191 --> 01:04:44,944
<i>Some are disarmed by childlike innocence.</i>

961
01:04:45,028 --> 01:04:46,279
BIOJEI 2027 OPEN RECRUITMENT

962
01:04:46,362 --> 01:04:47,238
Hello there.

963
01:04:48,114 --> 01:04:50,283
"Your diligent and responsible man."

964
01:04:50,366 --> 01:04:51,659
"I am Baek Gwang-nam."

965
01:04:52,285 --> 01:04:54,954
Your diligent and responsible man…

966
01:04:58,208 --> 01:05:00,710
K-beauty… The core of K-beauty.

967
01:05:00,793 --> 01:05:03,421
I dream of joining Biojei to be
at the frontline of K-beauty…

968
01:05:03,505 --> 01:05:04,881
That's not going to work.

969
01:05:05,423 --> 01:05:07,717
Frontline? Are you going off to war?

970
01:05:10,595 --> 01:05:12,889
Hey, I'm trying to rehearse here…

971
01:05:13,473 --> 01:05:14,474
What?

972
01:05:15,767 --> 01:05:16,643
Ji-hyo?

973
01:05:16,726 --> 01:05:17,852
Does she work here?

974
01:05:19,938 --> 01:05:22,941
Mr. Baek, are you seriously saying
this is your true calling?

975
01:05:23,024 --> 01:05:25,318
Wait, what are you doing here?

976
01:05:26,194 --> 01:05:27,654
-Are you here for me?
-No.

977
01:05:27,737 --> 01:05:28,738
Yeah.

978
01:05:28,821 --> 01:05:31,449
I'm here on business.
What a coincidence.

979
01:05:32,158 --> 01:05:33,660
Like destiny.

980
01:05:34,661 --> 01:05:37,789
Candidate 332, Mr. Baek Gwang-nam.

981
01:05:39,707 --> 01:05:40,833
Yes, I'm here.

982
01:05:40,917 --> 01:05:43,294
-You'll be next.
-Okay.

983
01:05:44,379 --> 01:05:45,838
Please excuse me, Ji-hyo.

984
01:05:47,090 --> 01:05:48,508
Don't go.

985
01:05:51,886 --> 01:05:53,054
Oh, my.

986
01:05:56,057 --> 01:05:58,393
Don't go. Work with me instead.

987
01:05:59,269 --> 01:06:01,020
-What?
-I'll triple your pay.

988
01:06:01,104 --> 01:06:02,188
Triple. Oh, my.

989
01:06:02,272 --> 01:06:03,314
I need

990
01:06:03,398 --> 01:06:04,774
a trash talker like you.

991
01:06:05,650 --> 01:06:07,193
Damn. What a baddie.

992
01:06:07,902 --> 01:06:09,153
Deal?

993
01:06:16,619 --> 01:06:20,873
<i>Some find meaning</i>
<i>in the calling of a name.</i>

994
01:06:20,957 --> 01:06:22,333
Congratulations, Se-gye.

995
01:06:22,834 --> 01:06:25,878
You've reclaimed the number one spot
in the Eastern European cosmetics market.

996
01:06:25,962 --> 01:06:27,171
Sorry about that, Tae-hee.

997
01:06:27,255 --> 01:06:30,258
You must've had quite a run
while I was stumbling.

998
01:06:30,883 --> 01:06:33,011
You don't look sorry at all.

999
01:06:33,636 --> 01:06:35,263
You actually look happy.

1000
01:06:35,346 --> 01:06:36,598
How annoying.

1001
01:06:38,433 --> 01:06:39,601
Yes, I am happy.

1002
01:06:40,310 --> 01:06:43,187
So happy I almost feel guilty about it.

1003
01:06:43,271 --> 01:06:44,647
What about you, Tae-hee?

1004
01:06:44,731 --> 01:06:46,441
I'm going to give happiness a try too.

1005
01:06:46,524 --> 01:06:48,151
Thanks to a certain someone,

1006
01:06:48,234 --> 01:06:50,486
I now believe
that such a thing really exists.

1007
01:06:52,780 --> 01:06:56,284
<i>Some carry hope for a new beginning.</i>

1008
01:06:56,367 --> 01:06:57,493
<i>Very well!</i>

1009
01:06:58,077 --> 01:07:00,496
<i>Let this day claim us both.</i>

1010
01:07:00,580 --> 01:07:03,541
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM 2

1011
01:07:03,625 --> 01:07:06,044
<i>Let us see this through!</i>

1012
01:07:06,127 --> 01:07:07,170
I mean,

1013
01:07:07,253 --> 01:07:09,631
that's just too much.
You can't claim cute,

1014
01:07:09,714 --> 01:07:11,799
pretty, and sexy all for yourself.

1015
01:07:11,883 --> 01:07:13,635
What's everyone else supposed to do?

1016
01:07:13,718 --> 01:07:16,596
Stop watching my old drama,
and help me run my lines.

1017
01:07:16,679 --> 01:07:17,764
Here.

1018
01:07:21,601 --> 01:07:23,144
-Your lines?
-Yeah.

1019
01:07:25,271 --> 01:07:27,482
Let's see. <i>My 99th First Kiss.</i>

1020
01:07:27,565 --> 01:07:29,150
What? Ninety…

1021
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:32,570
Are you saying
you're going to kiss 99 times?

1022
01:07:32,654 --> 01:07:33,863
Are you nuts?

1023
01:07:34,364 --> 01:07:35,657
No, don't do it. Cancel it.

1024
01:07:35,740 --> 01:07:37,283
Cancel what? The shoot is in two days.

1025
01:07:37,367 --> 01:07:38,242
Who cares?

1026
01:07:38,326 --> 01:07:41,204
I'll buy up all the ad spots.
Just take out all the kiss scenes.

1027
01:07:41,287 --> 01:07:43,623
"My 99th Eye Contact" sounds nice.
Family-friendly.

1028
01:07:43,706 --> 01:07:45,625
You must be kidding.
Who would watch that?

1029
01:07:45,708 --> 01:07:47,335
Are you trying to ruin my career?

1030
01:07:47,418 --> 01:07:48,294
What the…

1031
01:07:48,378 --> 01:07:49,879
Then you can just live with me.

1032
01:07:49,962 --> 01:07:51,673
I never agreed to that. Slow down.

1033
01:07:51,756 --> 01:07:53,091
Time for your kiss scene with me.

1034
01:07:53,174 --> 01:07:55,385
What are you doing? Stop it!

1035
01:07:57,095 --> 01:07:58,596
-It hurts.
-Are you okay?

1036
01:08:07,772 --> 01:08:09,524
<i>While others</i>

1037
01:08:10,400 --> 01:08:13,945
<i>find gratitude</i>
<i>for the smile of a loved one.</i>

1038
01:08:18,199 --> 01:08:20,743
<i>In this vast and boundless sea</i>
<i>we call life,</i>

1039
01:08:21,327 --> 01:08:24,414
<i>we survive</i>
<i>by holding onto whatever we can.</i>

1040
01:08:25,415 --> 01:08:28,042
Come spring, let us go see
the cornelian cherry flowers.

1041
01:08:28,126 --> 01:08:30,044
We will make flower pancakes.

1042
01:08:31,129 --> 01:08:33,381
-Flower pancakes?
-Yeah.

1043
01:08:34,090 --> 01:08:36,884
And in summer, we can come
to the sea, just like this.

1044
01:08:36,968 --> 01:08:38,511
And eat some ostrea too.

1045
01:08:38,594 --> 01:08:41,180
We should plant
trumpet vines in your yard.

1046
01:08:41,264 --> 01:08:43,141
And eat a whole lot of peaches.

1047
01:08:44,100 --> 01:08:46,018
Are we only going to plant and eat things?

1048
01:08:46,978 --> 01:08:49,439
Autumn calls for chrysanthemums.
We should plant some.

1049
01:08:49,522 --> 01:08:51,858
And a persimmon tree to pick from!

1050
01:08:52,650 --> 01:08:53,609
Unbelievable.

1051
01:08:54,610 --> 01:08:56,404
Our yard is going to become an orchard.

1052
01:08:56,487 --> 01:08:57,989
We'll be able to open a fruit stand.

1053
01:08:58,072 --> 01:08:59,949
Seasonal fruit is so good for you.

1054
01:09:00,825 --> 01:09:04,287
You find the little joys in life
when you eat what is in season.

1055
01:09:04,370 --> 01:09:06,247
Really? Who said that?

1056
01:09:06,789 --> 01:09:08,166
My grandma.

1057
01:09:08,249 --> 01:09:09,709
My grandma used to say that.

1058
01:09:09,792 --> 01:09:12,295
You have to enjoy things
in their time to be happy.

1059
01:09:13,463 --> 01:09:14,881
Happiness doesn't earn interest.

1060
01:09:16,424 --> 01:09:17,341
That's true.

1061
01:09:18,468 --> 01:09:19,343
It really is.

1062
01:09:20,720 --> 01:09:23,765
I am done lamenting the world.

1063
01:09:24,348 --> 01:09:25,683
I am going to live freely.

1064
01:09:26,225 --> 01:09:29,061
Like a pure white frost flower
in the middle of summer.

1065
01:09:29,145 --> 01:09:30,521
Freely.

1066
01:09:33,524 --> 01:09:35,109
Sure. Freely.

1067
01:09:37,445 --> 01:09:39,781
I love you, Shin Seo-ri.

1068
01:10:02,970 --> 01:10:06,140
<i>Empty tokens are meaningless.</i>
<i>Warmth is all you really need.</i>

1069
01:10:06,682 --> 01:10:10,353
<i>Having courage with every step</i>
<i>can keep you going in the end.</i>

1070
01:10:10,436 --> 01:10:12,146
<i>If you just hold on,</i>

1071
01:10:12,772 --> 01:10:15,691
<i>it will come to you, without fail.</i>

1072
01:10:27,870 --> 01:10:29,330
You beat me to it again.

1073
01:10:57,108 --> 01:10:58,526
<i>If you do,</i>

1074
01:10:59,443 --> 01:11:02,363
<i>a magnificent world</i>

1075
01:11:02,446 --> 01:11:04,907
<i>will unfold before you.</i>

1076
01:11:08,703 --> 01:11:11,372
<i>I guarantee it. You can trust me.</i>

1077
01:12:56,394 --> 01:12:58,396
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

